==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liliopsida
<hw>Liliopsida</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A class comprising seed plants
that produce an embryo with a single cotyledon and parallel-veined
leaves. It includes the grasses; lilies; palms; and orchids. It is
divided into four subclasses or superorders: Alismatidae; Arecidae;
Commelinidae; and Liliidae.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Monocotyledones, class Monocotyledones,
Monocotyledonae, class Monocotyledonae, class Liliopsida.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lilith</ent>⟦br⟧
